According to British media, General William Moran, Undersecretary of Warfare, said that even as the U.S. Navy is reviving its strength to tackle the increasingly worrying Russia on both sides of the Atlantic, the United States continues to make the Asia-Pacific region the scope of the region including the Indo-Pacific, the Pacific Ocean-Asia-Pacific a priority.
According to the website of Jane's Defense Weekly, the United States listed China and Russia as a strategic competitor in the new defense strategy announced at the beginning of the year.
The U.S. Navy has since restored the Second Fleet in order to more directly counter Russian activity.
The moves have raised some questions and concerns among allies and analysts who fear the U.S. Navy could stay away from the Obama administration's "Asia-Pacific rebalancing" strategy.
But Admiral Moran said the U.S. Navy's focus remains on the Western Pacific.
At a roundtable titled “Meeting the High Sea Challenge, ” hosted by the National Bureau of Asian Studies in Washington, D.C., on January 24, 2018, he said, “For us, no major changes have been changed. ”
Moran said, "The focus is still rebalancing, shifting the center of gravity or whatever you want to describe it," Moran said.
But he admits that the United States has close ties with Europe.
“We will continue to focus on the growth of the West Coast and balance what we can do, ” he said.
While Moran pointed out that the general policy on Russia falls within the purview of the U.S. defense secretary, he warned: "The Russians may face demographic and economic challenges, but history proves that if we conflict with them, they will be very tough."
Admiral Moran said that as part of the U.S. re-emergence operation against Russia, China and other competitors, the U.S. Navy is dynamically deploying troops into a "new operational mode" that will help get adversaries off guarding where U.S. carrier strike groups or other assets will be deployed at any given time.
“Our Navy and Marine Corps support it — the concept of operational unpredictability, not to appear in the same place again and again, almost like a clockwork — that ’ s what we do, ” he said.
The first attempt at this new approach was the "Harry Truman" carrier strike group, whose early deployments included working visits to ports and patrols in areas that are usually only adopted.
Moran said the U.S. Navy is currently working to make sure allies know that the warships will still be patrolling in traditional areas and is also addressing logistical and home liaison issues for the new deployment process.
Gen. Michael Noon, commander of the Royal Australian Navy, also spoke at the event, saying that the Australian army could work seamlessly with the US carrier strike group.
He said this situation would continue as the Royal Australian Navy plans to procure nine more frigates equipped with the Aegis operating system.
From October 5th, a number of airlines raised or restored fuel surcharges to increase the cost of air travel on Friday.
Yesterday, Xiangpeng Airlines, Okai Airlines and other airlines announced that since October 5, 2018 (the ticket date), the domestic route fuel surcharge of 800 km (including) the following routes will be charged 20 yuan fuel surcharge, and the 30 yuan fuel surcharge is charged per passenger per passenger on the 800km route.
Xiangpeng Airlines, Okai Airlines and other companies announced that since the zero o'clock (ticket date) on October 5, 2018, the tariff collection standard for fuel surcharges on domestic routes below 800 km has risen from 10 yuan / person to 20 yuan / person, and the fuel surcharge for domestic routes above 800km has risen from 10 yuan / person per passenger to 30 yuan / person.
Children and military police maims are 10 yuan / person; the baby continues to be exempted.
According to the relevant person in charge of Ctrip ticket, the airline has indicated in the notice that the collection of fuel surcharges is based on the original ticket date, and when the ticket is changed, the fuel surcharge is not refunded.
This means that domestic airline tickets issued before October 5th will not be required to make up for the fuel surcharge according to the new standard if they are to change until October 5th (inclusive) will be changed.
Since June 5, 2018, Air China, Eastern Airlines, HNA, Shanghai Airlines, Spring and Autumn Airlines, Shenzhen Airlines, Western Airlines, Okai Airlines and many other airlines have resumed charging fuel surcharges for domestic routes that have been cancelled for three years, and the standard is 10 yuan / person.
This time, Xiangpeng Airlines, Okai Airlines took the lead in announcing the increase in fuel surcharges, as of press time, has not seen the news of the announcement of the follow-up adjustment of the domestic 4 major airlines.
It is also understood that the Hong Kong Civil Aviation Department stipulates that airlines can decide for themselves from November on whether to charge a fuel surcharge.
Cathay Pacific announced at the earliest September 27th that it will recharge fuel surcharges from November 22nd.
According to the Cathay Pacific website, all tickets issued or reissued by Cathay Pacific and Cathay Dragon will include fuel surcharges for long-distance flights to Hong Kong and the South West Pacific, North America, Europe, the Middle East and India, and Africa, with fuel surcharges of 652 yuan and 146 yuan for short-haul flights.
The fee is available for all types of tickets, calculated in each segment and included in the Cathay Pacific ticket quote on all direct sales channels.
On the even of the 69th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China, Chinese Premier Li Keqiang met with the new ambassadors of 29 countries and the region at the Great Hall of the People on the afternoon of the 30th.
Li Keqiang shook hands and had a cordial conversation with the envoys in China one by one.
Li Keqiang welcomed the envoys to take their new role in China and asked them to convey their sincere greetings and best wishes to the leaders and leaders of relevant countries and relevant institutions.
Li Keqiang spoke positively of China's good relations with other countries and regions, stressing that China is committed to enhancing bilateral political mutual trust, deepening practical cooperation, and strengthening coordination and cooperation in international and regional affairs. He hoped that the envoys would walk more and see more and make new positive contributions to promoting the development of China's relations with their respective countries and regions in their new posts.
The Chinese Government is willing to facilitate and support the envoys in performing their duties.
Li Keqiang pointed out that China adheres to the path of peaceful development and unswervingly promotes economic globalization.
This year marks the 40th anniversary of China's reform and opening up. As the world's largest developing country, we are willing to achieve common development with other countries in the further expansion of opening-up.
Against the background of the rise of protectionism and unilateralism, we are willing to work with all parties to continue to consolidate and strengthen partnerships in the spirit of mutual respect, equality and mutual benefit, promote docking development strategies, promote the Belt and Road construction and cooperation in the principle of consultation, joint construction and sharing, jointly safeguard multilateralism and free trade, and jointly build an open world economy, so as to inject new impetus into the stable and balanced development of the world economy.
The envoys of various countries and institutions in China warmly congratulate the People's Republic of China on the 69th anniversary, convey the greetings of leaders of their respective countries and institutions to the Chinese leaders and the people, and said that China's development achievements have been remarkable, and we believe that further deepening reform and opening up in the future will bring more development opportunities to the world.
We are willing to play a positive role in promoting friendly cooperation between their countries and regions with China and better achieving mutual benefit and win-win results.
Subsequently, the embassies of various countries and institutions in China attended the National Day reception at the invitation of Li Keqiang.
State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi attended the event.
Japan's Ito Zhong Commercial on Friday identified a $13 billion in impairment losses in investment in China's China CITIC shares, a write-down of the largest corporate investment deal due to trade tensions between China and the United States.
In Tokyo, Japan, in May 2016, a man walked past the headquarters of Marubeni Co., Ltd.
Marubeni said that the trade war hit Gao Hong, the U.S. grain division, and that it has suspended financial transactions in agriculture.
In the past, some heavy equipment manufacturers and telecommunications companies in Japan have issued warnings about the impact of Sino-US trade frictions at the time of the latest results, and now these Japanese traders have joined the ranks.
The United States and China have imposed tariffs on each other's hundreds of billions of dollars of goods, and U.S. President Donald Trump has threatened that if the dispute cannot be resolved, the levy will be extended to all of more than $50 billion of Chinese exports to the United States.
Ito Zhong's chief financial minister, Tsuyoshi Hachimura, said the impact of the trade dispute on China's economy could be even greater next year.
Ito Zhong Commercial and Thailand's Bu Bee Group invested $10 billion in the 2015 to gain a 20 percent stake in CITIC.
Hachimura said that Ito Zhong Commercial's shareholding in this part of the column was a loss of 1,443 billion yen ($1.3 billion) in view of the fact that CITIC's stock price will not pick up in the near future.
Ito Zhong Commercial maintained a profit forecast for the fiscal year ending March 31, 2019 at 5,000 billion yen.
