“Our grain business has been hit by U.S.-China trade frictions, ” said Yan Hong, the Treasurer of Marubeni.
He said Gao Hong had stopped trading financial transactions on his own account since September.
Gao Hong spokesman Pat Burke said in a statement on Friday that the company's move was "consistent in accordance with internal policy restrictions and due to a lack of market opportunities."
He also said that the suspension of financial transactions would not lead to job losses.
Marubeni remained unchanged for its annual profit estimate of 2,300 billion yen, which was helped by the pulp and paper and power generation business.
Sumitomo announced a 16 percent increase in profit from April to September on Thursday, stressing that “America ’ s trade issues with China have left the outlook uncertain. ”
Mitsubishi Motors on Friday raised its annual profit forecast to record levels, at a drop of increased coking coal production and higher prices for commodities such as oil and coal.
Mitsubishi Corporation also announced a new business plan, aiming to increase its profit in the fiscal year ending March 31, 2022 to increase from the 6,400 billion yen ($79.8 billion) estimated this year.
