Under the current wave of "mass entrepreneurship, innovation", more and more technology companies have begun to attach importance to patent research and development and related protection work, digging deep into the potential value of patents, and occupying market dominance.
Similarly, there are many technology companies that have encountered no small infringement storm in terms of patent technology licensing and patent technology use.
At the end of 2017, Tan Wei, He Zhanghong and Lai Bin from Guangdong Province three people took the "Didi Chuxing" APP developer Beijing Xiaolan Technology Co., Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as Xiaotang Technology), the operator Didi Chuxing Technology Co., Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as Didi Chuxing), and the seller of Guangdong Pacific Internet Information Service Co., Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as Guangdong Pacific) to the Guangzhou Intellectual Property Court.
The three plaintiffs requested a court order that the three defendants immediately cease the patent behavior of manufacturing, selling, promising sales, and using the plaintiff's patent.
On October 30, 2018, the China Referee Instrument Network published the "Olimate Judgment of the First Instance Dispute between Tan Wei, He Zhanghong and Beijing Xiaotang Technology Co., Ltd.", and disclosed the details of some cases of Didi Chuxing APP for patent infringement.
The three plaintiffs believe that the patent and inventor of the patent and inventor of the "mobile ride-sharing service system and method-based" patent, and the entire operation process of the "Shunfeng" application in the "Didi Chuxing" APP corresponds to the technical scheme of patent protection in the case, which constitutes a patent infringement.
However, during the court's ruling, Xiaolan Technology believes that Guangdong Pacific is not a qualified defendant, and it only provides a free download of the APP "drip trip" on the Internet, and does not implement the patent method involved in the case, there is no direct or indirect infringement, and should not be listed as the defendant in this case.
Second, the violation of this case is not in Guangdong.
According to the law, the place of infringement of the patent in question shall be the place where the patent method involved is carried out in full, so it has raised an objection to the jurisdiction of the court and requires that the case be transferred to the court of the defendant's domicile, the Beijing Intellectual Property Court for hearing.
The Guangzhou Intellectual Property Court held that the defendant Guangdong Pacific provided the accused of infringing Didi Chuxing APP products on its online platform, and the plaintiff did not make it inappropriate to list the defendant Guangdong Pacific as the defendant.
And the defendant's Guangdong Pacific residence is located in Guangzhou, which is within the jurisdiction of the Guangzhou Intellectual Property Court.
Defendant Xiao Orange Technology claims to transfer the case to the Beijing Intellectual Property Court for trial, on the basis of the lack of time, dismiss the defendant Xiaotang Technology Co., Ltd.'s objections to the jurisdiction of the case, and bear the cost of the acceptance of the jurisdictional objection case.
At present, other trials of the case have not been announced, and the reporter will also pay close attention to the follow-up details of Didi Chuxing's patent infringement case.
Interview with Chief Executive Officer of the Commonwealth Scientific and Industrial Research Organization of Australia: Significant achievements in Australia-China Science and Technology Cooperation
"China's science and technology have developed rapidly in the past few decades, and Australia and China have worked hand in hand in the scientific field to achieve fruitful results."
Larry Marshall, chief executive of the Commonwealth Scientific and Industrial Research Organisation of Australia, said in an interview with the China News Agency in Beijing that from the cooperation on climate change to the "Sky Eye" project, the cooperation between Australia and China in science and technology has shown vitality.
As the largest national research institution in the Australian Federation, CSIRO has achieved many innovative research results in the world in the fields of oceans, energy, biology, materials, astronomy and so on.
CSIRO has maintained close cooperation with scientific research institutions such as the Chinese Academy of Sciences.
"It's a lasting friendship that encompasses a tradition of trust and long-term cooperation for partners," Marshall said.
In May this year, China's 500-meter-caliber spherical radio telescope, "China Sky Eye", installed the world's first 19-wave beam L band receiver.
At present, the most advanced 19-wave beam feeder receiver in the world, jointly developed by Chinese and Australian scientists.
Marshall said that the successful development of the receiver is based on the accumulation of technology from CSIRO for many years, and after the launch, the FAST sky survey speed will be increased by five to six times, and at the same time, it will also expand more scientific observation goals.
"This is a part of the CSIRO's contribution to FAST."
In addition to the above-mentioned cooperation, CSIRO also has close cooperation with Chinese scientific research institutions in the construction of square kilometers array radio telescopes, research and development of new fuel technology, and energy conservation and emission reduction.
"In the past, scientific research often focused on the problems of the past hundred years, and now more scientific research force is needed to solve the problems in front of us."
Marshall believes that Australia and China are complementary in the field of scientific development, and both countries face a series of challenges in their development.
For example, extreme weather is frequent in the world, droughts and floods have led to food production cuts, and food shortages have seriously affected human development.
At the same time, problems such as population explosion, aging, and chronic diseases are also the serious challenges facing them.
"The cooperation between Australia and China in recent years is mainly focused on solving these current problems."
Marshall said that the International Southern Hemisphere Marine Research Center, built by CSIRO and the National Laboratory of Marine Science and Technology of Qingdao, focuses on observing the El Niño phenomenon and the La Niña phenomenon, studying the relationship between the two and extreme weather, and establishing an early warning facility for extreme weather; the new varieties of cereals developed by the CSIRO and the Chinese Academy of Sciences can also alleviate the food shortage caused by extreme weather.
"In the current environment, scientific and technological innovation is difficult to complete alone, the need for extremely high cost, there are very many problems to be solved, so cooperation is particularly important today."
Marshall said that the closer the cooperation, the more likely it is to make a breakthrough, which is also the significance of strengthening cooperation between Australia and China under the framework of the Belt and Road Initiative.
"Strengthening bilateral cooperation is mainly for us to cooperate in science and technology."
Marshall, for example, said that CSIRO has developed a purening method of gold without cyanide, which is very harmful to the environment due to the traditional cyanide gold purification method, and many countries hope to find a way to purify gold with little environmental pollution.
"We are very willing to bring this technology to China, which is one of the results of our participation in the Belt and Road cooperation."
