North Korean Foreign Minister Ri Yong Ho said Saturday that the continued imposition of sanctions has deepened North Korea's distrust of the United States, and it is impossible for North Korea to unilaterally give up its nuclear weapons under such circumstances.
Speaking at the U.N. General Assembly, Ri said North Korea had taken a "very friendly approach" over the past year, including halting missile and nuclear tests, dismantling nuclear testing sites, and pledging to non-proliferation of nuclear weapons and nuclear technology.
"But we don't see any corresponding response from the United States," he said.
"If we don't trust the United States, there is no confidence in our national security, and in such a situation, we can't give up our weapons unilaterally first."
While Rie is repeating North Korea's complaint about U.S. opposition to "phased" denuclearization, his speech is of great significance because it does not completely reject unilateral denuclearization, as North Korea did before.
Li Yong Ho mentioned a joint statement between Kim and Trump on June 12th, when Kim Jong Un agreed to the "denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula" effort, and Trump promised to protect North Korea's security.
North Korea has been seeking to formally end the 1950-53 Korean War, but the United States says North Korea must first give up its nuclear weapons.
The United States has also refused to ease its demands for international sanctions against North Korea.
"The United States insists on 'denuclearization first' and ramps up sanctions pressure to achieve its goals in a high-pressure manner, and even refuses to issue a 'declaration of war ending'," Li Yongho said.
"The idea that sanctions can make us kneel for forgiveness is to not understand our people's daydreams."
But the problem is that such persistent sanctions are deepening our distrust. ”
Li Yong-ho did not mention the second Trump trip by the US president mentioned earlier this week at the United Nations.
Instead, he highlighted the meeting between Kim Jong Un and South Korean President Moon Jae-in three times in the past five months and said: “If the other side of denuclearisation is South Korea, not North Korea, then the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula will not become so deadlocked. ”
China announced that it has reduced import duties on 1585 tax items since November 1, 2018.
Since the beginning of this year, China has successively taken the initiative to reduce import tariffs.
On May 1st this year, the drug was comprehensively reduced, and the import tariff for a total of 28 tax purposes, including all ordinary drugs and co-alkali drugs with anti-cancer effects, and a total of 28 tax items such as Chinese medicine imported.
At the same time, it has also significantly reduced the value-added tax burden of anti-cancer drug production and import links.
On July 11th, the car and parts for the purpose of the tax were reduced.
After the tax reduction, China's automobile vehicle tax rate has been lower than the average in developing countries, in line with the actual situation of China's automobile industry.
This tax reduction will promote the structural adjustment of the industry and the optimal allocation of resources, accelerate the survival of the fittest, help to improve the quality of products and services, and is expected to promote the adjustment of automobile prices to a certain extent, so that consumers can get more benefits.
On July 1st, the tax on 1449 taxes was taxed for daily consumer goods.
The tax reduction of daily consumer goods is closely related to the people's needs for a better life.
This tax reduction is not only a large number but also strong, the average tax reduction has reached 56%.
The tax reduction of daily consumer goods directly benefits the majority of consumers and promotes the competitiveness of domestic industries.
On November 11th, the tax reduction will be implemented on November 11th for industrial products such as machinery and electrical equipment, parts and raw materials for 1585 tax purposes.
Appropriately reducing import tariffs on some of the much-needed domestic industrial products can attract more foreign investment, which is conducive to increasing domestic supply and helping industries to upgrade, while helping enterprises to allocate resources on a global scale, reducing production costs, and reducing the pressure on the domestic environment.
The relevant person in charge of the Office of the Tariff and Tax Committee of the State Council of China introduced that the above four independent tax cuts, as well as the third step of tax reduction implemented under the results of the negotiations on July 11th under the scope of the information technology agreement, will reduce the total tariff level of China from 9.8% to 7.5% in the previous year.
