Kosovo became the "powderpow keg" in the Balkans.
In 1999, an armed conflict between Albanian separatists in the Kosovo Liberation Army and the Serbian army and police led to the bombing of the Federal Republic of Serbia and Montenegro by NATO forces, which broke out in the Kosovo War.
On February 17, 2008, Kosovo unilaterally declared its independence from Serbia.
Since then, although there is news that Serbia will normalize relations with Kosovo and sign a global and legally binding agreement, it has not been possible to sign an agreement subject to multiple forces such as the United States, Europe and Russia due to historical national grievances and geopolitical constraints.
