Nearly a thousand state-owned scenic spots cut ticket prices by more than half of them reduced by more than 20%
[Abstract] As of September 28th, all localities have introduced or issued documents to the public to publish 981 scenic spots free open or price reduction measures (free open 74, price reduction of 907), Yunnan Shilin, Dali three towers, Yulong Snow Mountain, Guangxi Guilin Lijiang, Fujian Wuyishan, Hunan Zhangjiajie, Shaanxi Terracotta, Jiangxi Sanqingshan, Xinjiang Kanas and other scenic spots have implemented price reduction.
In order to implement the decision-making and deployment of the Central Economic Work Conference and the "Government Work Report", the National Development and Reform Commission issued the "Guidance on Improving the Price of State-owned Scenic Area Ticketing Mechanism to Reduce the Ticket Price of Key State-owned Scenic Areas" (hereinafter referred to as the Guiding Opinions), which requires the reasonable definition of ticket pricing cost composition, innovative price management methods, and strict implementation of pricing procedures, etc.
All localities have actively carried out their work in accordance with the deployment requirements, and have successively reduced the ticket price of a number of key state-owned scenic spots.
As of September 28th, all localities have introduced or issued documents to the public to publish 981 scenic free or open or price reduction measures (free open 74, price reduction 907), of which 159 A-level scenic spots, 4A scenic spots 534, the two total 693, accounting for 70.6%.
Of the 907 scenic spots with price cuts, the decrease was more than 20%, accounting for 54.3 per cent, and the decrease was more than 30%, accounting for 23.6%.
Yunnan, Shandong, Guangxi, Shaanxi and other provinces have a large number of price reduction scenic spots, of which the number of price-reducing scenic spots in Yunnan has been reduced by more than one hundred, and the overall reduction is more than 30%.
Anhui, Chongqing and other eight provinces (districts, cities) government pricing 5A scenic spots all to achieve price reduction.
The high degree of social concern of Yunnan Shilin, Dali Santa, Yulong Snow Mountain, Guangxi Lin Lijiang, Fujian Wuyishan, Hunan Zhangjiajie, Shaanxi Terracotta Army, Jiangxi Sanqingshan, Xinjiang Kanas and other scenic spots have implemented price cuts.
The gradual return of ticket prices to a reasonable range of key state-owned scenic spots is conducive to accelerating the transformation and upgrading of tourism from the ticket economy to the industrial economy, niche tourism to mass tourism, and attraction tourism to global tourism, which is conducive to forming a virtuous circle of tourism supply structure optimization and the steady expansion of tourism consumption demand, and promoting the sustainable and healthy development of scenic spots and tourism.
At the same time, the National Development and Reform Commission stressed that all localities should strengthen the price order norms of scenic spots, guide scenic spots to upgrade services, and ensure that prices are not reduced.
In addition, for the recent media reflect the price of individual scenic spots ticket prices too small and clear and not down the problem, the National Development and Reform Commission has carried out special supervision, requiring all localities to deal with seriously, timely response to social concerns, and effectively put in place price reduction.
Trade Promotion Bureau to carry out short-, medium and long-term optimization work in an orderly manner
The Macao Trade and Investment Promotion Bureau has submitted a short, medium- and long-term optimization report on "major investment migration" and "skilled migration", and in addition to stepping up and implementing the work in the report, it has also been continuously listening to the views of the society and continuously optimizing the content of the report and related work.
The Trade Promotion Bureau will introduce relevant optimization efforts to all sectors of society as soon as possible.
Five of them are short-term measures carried out within this year; five are medium-term measures carried out in 2019; and one is a long-term measure.
In addition, the Trade Promotion Bureau has also conducted a comprehensive review of the internal management system in accordance with the instructions of the Secretary for Economic and Financial Affairs, Liang Witt.
Five short-term measures carried out this year include:
1. Carry out the review process. Priority shall be given to the cases that will expire for the seven years, the cases referred to in the report of the CCAC, and the newly resurgent cases. If cases are found to be inappropriate or illegal, they will take the initiative to refer to the relevant judicial organs for follow-up;
2. Field inspections of projects involving “significant investment migrants ”, which have been inspected by late September over 20 investment projects;
3. A comprehensive review of the current review system. In the review of the "major investment immigration" application, six principles for the analysis of investment projects have been re-established; in the evaluation of "technical immigration" applications, the relevant approval mechanism will be improved by clarifying the elements conducive to the development of Macao and the conditions for the priority of the absorption of talents. At the same time, the "five industry ten types of work" for the annual priority introduction of talents have been set, in order to cooperate with the governance direction of the SAR government and more targeted to absorb talents;
4. Continuously increase the transparency of information, including the plan to gradually publish approval criteria, scoring standards and proportions from the fourth quarter of this year, and further refine and disclose the data for approval;
5. In terms of improving the work of the confirmation mechanism, it has been requested to check the work in Australia before confirming; the major investment must be on-site to check and submit the financial statements.
Five medium-term measures carried out in 2019 include:
1. Establish a mechanism to regularly hear the views of the Talent Development Committee and the Economic Development Committee, which has held a working meeting with the Economic Development Committee in September to discuss the establishment of relevant mechanisms.
2. Requires the applicant to submit annual financial statements made by an independent third party to keep a review of the operating status of the investment project;
3. Further standardize and electronicize the process of case application and approval in order to reduce human error;
4. Comprehensive review of the current staffing configuration, with a number of optimization measures;
5. Intensify the study of the Temporary Residence System for Investors, Managers and Specially Qualified Technical Personnel.
As for the long-term measures, the study of revision is expected to be carried out in the first half of 2019, and the relevant regulations are drafted, and the approval criteria, review mechanism and confirmation mechanism for temporary residence permits will be further clarified, and the investigation function of the Trade Promotion Bureau will be increased to more accurately approve and supervise the application for temporary residence permits.
Experts from the national membrane-free cotton on-site observation and discussion and exchange activities walked into the test field and listened to the representative of the academician team of the Chinese Academy of Engineering.
China New Network Xinjiang Shaya September 30th (Gengdandan Wang Xiaojun) is located in Xinjiang Shaya County, the filmless cotton growth is gratifying, compared with the mulch cotton next to the mulch cotton "unbeatable", a cluster of snow-white cotton competing "open", hanging branches.
From September 27th to 28th, the national in-person inspection and discussion and exchange activities were held in Shaya County, Xinjiang.
The reporter learned at the observation meeting that the membrane-free cotton technology system with "Chinese cotton619" and its supporting cultivation measures has initially achieved the goal of membrane-free cultivation of cotton fields, reducing the pollution of the ecological environment and raw cotton of the cotton field in Xinjiang, and making significant progress in the research and demonstration of the comprehensive technology of the membrane-free cotton.
Academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, the famous cotton genetic breeder, and the chief scientist of the cotton system of the national modern agricultural industry technology system, Yu Shuxun, introduced the growth of membrane-free cotton to Zhou Guomou, party secretary of Zhejiang Agricultural and Forestry University.
"The comprehensive technology we have developed for membrane-free cotton can be fully realized to plant cotton without mulch, which can completely solve the problem of residual film pollution and achieve green cotton planting."
The academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, Yu Shuxun, introduced.
Xinjiang is China's most important cotton-producing region. According to the National Bureau of Statistics, the cotton cultivation area in Xinjiang was 35 million acres in 2017, accounting for 61 percent of the country's cotton area.
Since the introduction of mulch into China in 1982, the area of all kinds of crop film in Xinjiang has reached more than 50 million acres, and the annual use of the mulch is about 30 million tons.
Among them, the coverage of cotton film covers up to 100%, and cotton field coverings account for about 60% of the use of mulch in Xinjiang.
Imethless cotton is measured, and cotton production can be produced by 320kg to 350kg.
With the continuous increase of the input of the mulch in Xinjiang, the recycling rate of residual film is low, the amount of residual film in the soil is gradually increasing, and the amount of soil structure damage caused by the residual film has seriously affected the sustainable development of agriculture.
The disresult is not only causing serious pollution to the soil, but also has a great impact on the quality of the cotton fiber.
At present, the cotton fields that exceed draped over draped in Xinjiang have achieved mechanized harvest.
In 2017, the area of cotton mining in Xinjiang was about 14 million acres.
Machine mining cotton harvest process income a large number of surface, cotton on the broken film, doped in the original cotton in the process of raw cotton processing is difficult to remove, in the follow-up textile processing process can not be completely removed, seriously affecting the quality of textile products.
On September 28th, the national forless filmless cotton site observation and discussion and exchange activities were held in Shaya County, Xinjiang.
In order to focus on solving the pollution of cotton field membranes, simplifying cotton planting technology, and improving the efficiency of cotton fields, Yu Shuxun led his team to implement the "China Cotton619" membrane-free cotton technology cultivation for the green development of Xinjiang.
Through innovative breeding new ideas, we have cultivated a new line of land cotton "Chinese cotton619" through innovative breeding new ideas, salt-tolerant, low temperature resistance and abundant land cotton.
"The" China Cotton619 "has realized a series of supporting measures such as membrane-free planting machinery, improved the depth of seeding, drip strip shallow burial under membraneless conditions, suitable sowing density screening, and reasonable chemical regulation."
At present, Aksu, Kurle, Arar and other places have established a membrane-free cotton demonstration base, and the yield per hectare has reached 4800 kilograms.
Irco-free planting cotton, to achieve abundant production, cost-saving, environmental protection, comprehensive efficiency improvement.
Zhang Donghai, an agronomist of the Third Division Agricultural Science Institute of the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, said that through the research and demonstration of membrane-free cotton cultivation technology in the past six years, the production of non-filmd cotton seeds can fully produce 320kg to 350kg, and may even be higher.
"The promotion of membrane-free cotton cultivation technology is very promising."
Zhang Donghai believes that at present, membraneless cotton cultivation technology can completely solve the problem of soil residual film pollution, but at present, there is still a certain gap between the economic benefits compared to the mulch cultivation.
"The support of the purchase price of cotton will be conducive to future promotion."
Yu Shuxun said that in the next step, he and his team will continue to conduct in-depth research and large-scale promotion and application of membrane-free cotton, so as to make the film-free cotton industry bigger and stronger, and completely solve the problem of soil pollution caused by the mulch.
