Xinhua News Agency, Fuzhou, October 1st (Reporter) On October 1st, the "Regulations on the Safety Management of High-speed Railways in Fujian Province" were officially implemented.
The regulations propose that air drifts and small aircraft such as jets such as kites, balloons, Kongming lamps, and aircraft are prohibited in the range of each of the 500m meters of the wires of high-speed rail power lines.
On the basis of the upper law such as the Railway Law of the People's Republic of China and the Regulations on the Administration of Railway Safety, according to the characteristics of the geographical and climatic conditions of Fujian Province, supplement the prohibition and restriction of the safety of high-speed rail, regulate the construction of construction and tree planting along the high-speed railway, further clarify the main body and scope of supervision of the high-speed railway, and clarify the responsibilities and legal responsibilities of law enforcement and supervision.
The regulations for the large wind in the coastal high-speed province, the situation of light construction (structure) building materials and light drifts blown into the high-speed rail affect the safety of the high-speed rail, and the high-speed rail power line is stipulated in the range of each of the 500 meters on both sides of the high-speed rail line, and it is prohibited to lift the flying kites, balloons, Kongming lamps, power umbrellas, aircraft and other air drifts and mini aircraft.
In addition, along the high-speed rail along the plastic greenhouses, colored steel plates, sunnets and other light objects and light drifts produced during the construction process, all owners or users should take reinforcement protection measures to prevent high-speed railway safety.
In view of the characteristics of Fujian Province in hilly areas and high-speed railway tunnels, the regulations require the construction of mountain ponds, reservoirs, levees, excavations, and wells that may affect the safety of tunnels in the area of the high-speed rail tunnel on the upper and eastern parts of the center line, and should be consulted by railway construction units or railway transport enterprises.
At the same time, the person responsible for violating the Regulations shall be ordered to be corrected by the public security organ; if the circumstances are more serious, the unit shall be fined up to more than 5,000 yuan and less than ten thousand yuan, and the fine of more than 200 yuan and less than five thousand yuan shall be imposed on the unit; if the circumstances are serious, the unit shall be imposed and a fine of more than ten thousand yuan or less than 1000 yuan shall be imposed on the individual, and the fine of more than 500 yuan and more than 1000 yuan shall be imposed on the individual.
Where such losses are caused, they shall be liable in accordance with the law.
It is understood that with the rapid development of railway construction, the high-speed railway mileage of 200km / h and above in Fujian Province has reached 1516 kilometers per hour, and the city-to-city railway has been realized, and it is expected that the 200km / h per hour of 20km per hour and above in Fujian will reach 2150 kilometers.
The implementation of this provision will standardize the safety management of high-speed rail in Fujian Province, further implement the responsibilities of local government departments, coordinate railways and local forces, work together to ensure the safety of high-speed rail, and improve the high-speed rail safety prevention and control system in Fujian Province.
HONG KONG, Nov 5 (Reuters) - China's largest beer producer, China's largest beer producer (0291.HK), announced on Monday that it had acquired six brewery established in the mainland through its Chinarun Snow B beer (Hineken / Heenigan) (HIN.AS) and all of its issued share capital in Heineken / Heenigen (HEIN.AS) in the mainland, with a total cost of about HK $23.55 billion.
