One case of H5N6 bird flu confirmed in Guangdong province
The Health Bureau said that according to the latest notification from the mainland health department, a single case of human infection with H5N6 avian influenza was confirmed in Guangdong province.
The Health Department is calling on residents to avoid contact with birds and pay attention to personal and food hygiene.
According to the data, the patient is a 22-year-old man, now living in Baiyun District, Guangzhou, Guangdong Province; on September 25, fever and other symptoms, September 26th hospital treatment, is currently in isolation in the hospital, the condition is critical.
The patient killed and consumed live poultry before the onset of the disease.
Since April 2014, there have been confirmed cases of H5N6 avian influenza in Sichuan, Guangdong, Yunnan, Hubei, Hunan, Anhui and Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Regions.
The Health Department will continue to maintain close contact with the health departments and the World Health Organization in the country and neighboring regions to closely monitor the outbreak in various places and in Macao.
In order to prevent human infection with avian influenza, the Health Bureau calls on the public to pay attention to the following matters:
Avoid contact with birds or secretions or excretions; if you have contact, wash your hands immediately;
Do not buy or carry unsanitary birds;
Do not eat untied birds and birds, internal organs, blood products and eggs;
Pay attention to personal hygiene and wash your hands frequently;
If you have symptoms such as fever, cough, and difficulty breathing, you should wear a mask, seek medical attention as soon as possible, and detail the history of travel and animal contact with the doctor.
