China and Pakistan agree to complete the construction of the economic corridor in a timely manner and speed up the construction of Gwadar Port
China and Pakistan agreed to further consolidate and expand economic ties between the two countries, the Chinese Foreign Ministry said on Sunday.
China and Pakistan issued a joint statement on Sunday to further strengthen the strategic partnership.
The two sides reaffirmed their "commitment to the construction of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor" and "oppose the negative publicity of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor".
Reuters quoted China's foreign ministry as saying that China and Pakistan will "strengthen practical cooperation in the field of trade and investment, and enhance Pakistan's industrial capacity by setting up joint ventures in priority areas, transferring labor-intensive industries and carrying out SME cooperation."
A press release published on the website of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs said that the two sides agreed to complete the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor under construction in a timely manner, accelerate the construction of ports and supporting projects in Gwadar Port, focus on economic and social development, create employment and improve people's livelihood, and accelerate cooperation in the fields of industry and parks and agriculture.
"The two sides agreed to complete the second phase of the China-Pakistan Free Trade Agreement negotiations as soon as possible and continue to advance the negotiations on the China-Pakistan Service Trade Agreement," he said.
In a joint statement signed on Sunday, the two sides reaffirmed their commitment to the construction of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor and agreed that the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor is a win-win plan for win-win cooperation, which will promote regional connectivity and bring prosperity and development to the entire region.
The two sides agreed that Gwadar Port is an important node in cross-regional connectivity and a pillar of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor.
The two sides agreed to speed up the construction of the port and supporting projects of the Gwadar port.
China and Pakistan also expressed their opposition to negative publicity against the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor.
The two sides agreed to establish a China-Pakistan Foreign Minister's Strategic Dialogue and adjust the original strategic dialogue at the level of deputy foreign ministers to diplomatic consultations.
In addition, the two countries will further strengthen defense cooperation and maintain high-level exchanges of military visits and exchanges between various departments and departments and levels.
