The reporter learned from the National Health and Health Commission that compared with a few decades ago, the incidence of malnutrition among children and adolescents in China has declined, but the incidence of overweight and obesity has increased significantly.
Experts pointed out that the main idea of maintaining a healthy weight is to "cure the disease" and vigorously promote scientific fitness and reasonable meals.
According to the "China Youth Health Education Core Information and Interpretation (2018 Edition)" released recently by the National Health and Health Commission, the key to maintaining a healthy weight is reasonable diet and scientific exercise.
Being overweight, obesity and blind weight loss are not good for health.
The health risks behind the "little fat pier" cannot be ignored.
Ding Gangqiang, director of the Nutrition and Health Institute of the China Center for Disease Control and Prevention, said that overweight obesity endangers the normal growth and development of adolescents, has adverse effects on their psychology, behavior, cognition and intelligence, and even leads to high blood pressure, high blood sugar, and high blood lipids in children.
At the same time, the high-grade obesity of adolescents is likely to continue into adulthood, which will increase the risk of chronic diseases such as high blood pressure and diabetes in adults.
Ding Gangqiang said that the nutrition and health status test of Chinese residents in 2010-2012 shows that the overweight rate of children and adolescents aged 6-17 years in China is 9.6%, the obesity rate is 6.4%, and the two are added to 16%.
At the same time, children and adolescents overweight and obesity show that boys are higher than girls, urban higher than rural characteristics, overweight obesity rate has increased significantly in recent decades.
How do teenagers deal with overweight obesity?
Zhang Li, deputy director of the Scientific Fitness and Health Promotion Research Center of the State Sports Administration, pointed out that the main reason for the current obesity of adolescents is that the main reason for obesity in adolescents is that there is too much caloric intake and insufficient physical activity.
For this simple obesity, should focus on scientific exercise plus reasonable diet control.
Zhang Li pointed out that the main concept of maintaining a healthy weight, the most important concept is "treating the disease", which is an important part of the school, parents and students to carry out a full range of popular science education, popularize the harm of overweight and obesity, and improve the awareness of young people's prevention.
