China News Agency Yichang October 1st (Guo Xiaoying Liu Min) newly revised "Three Gorges - Gezhouba Water Conservancy Hub navigation and dispatch Regulations" (hereinafter referred to as the "dispatch procedure") officially began to be implemented from October 1st, the Three Gorges lift in the trial of navigation, officially unified with the locks of dispatch.
On the first day of the implementation of the new regulations, the waters of the Three Gorges-Gezhou Dam were in good order.
The Yangtze River Three Gorges Navigation Authority issued its first security inspection plan on September 30th, and screened 160 ships, and a total of 124 ship security checks were qualified.
On October 11th, 14th, the navigable department arranged the first crossing plan after the implementation of the new regulations.
After the implementation of the new regulations, the security plan is issued once every day at 9am and 21st, and the dam plan is issued once per day and 20 hours, so that the ship can flexibly arrange the dam plan.
The "Dispatch Procedure" adds the principle of "classification control" of ship over-the-saw and dam dispatch, which clearly defines the ship's priority of the dam according to the functional positioning of the lock and the lift, and adjusts the short-term passenger ship that passes the lock to the same priority level as the demonstration ship and the integrity ship.
This is also a two-thirmination after the commissioning of the lift, and the locks are officially unified.
The Sichuan River and the Three Gorges Reservoir District, the long-sized and new energy power ships have also been among the priority levels for the first time.
At the same time, the "Severaling Regulations" adjust the "navigable dispatch management waters" from the previously 180km near the dam waters to the Yunyang Yangtze River Bridge to the 541.8 kilometers of waters of the Shilong River Bridge, and divides the "core waters, near-dam waters, control waters, and dispatch waters".
This will help the ship choose the appropriate waters to be located in the lock and reduce the backlog of ships in the dam area to be located.
The "Dispatching Regulations" also put forward good faith restrictions such as the cancellation declaration of ships in violation of the violation and delaying the 24-hour dam over the dam according to the characteristics of the current ship crossing and the pending gate.
After the water storage in the Three Gorges, the navigation conditions in the reservoir area have been improved, which has promoted the rapid development of Yangtze River shipping.
The data shows that the annual cargo passage volume of the Three Gorges locks and Gezhou Dam locks has increased from 34.30 million tons in 2004 to 1.38 million tons and 1.4 billion tons in 2017, respectively.
Three Gorges lift test voyage in the past two years through the ship 5767 times, passengers 16.22 million people, cargo volume reached 171.28 million tons.
Chen Dongyuan, deputy director of the Three Gorges Navigation Administration, said that the "Settlement Procedure" has a positive effect on promoting the management of the gate in good faith, maintaining the order of navigation of the two dam hubs, easing the pressure of the ship waiting for the gate in the dam area, and improving the navigation ability.
