Inner Mongolia import and export links of 46 kinds of regulatory certificates all to achieve network verification - China New Network
China New Network Hohhot November 5th (Reporter Li Aiping) Hohhot Customs said on the 5th that from now on, in addition to the need for confidentiality and other special circumstances, all 46 types of local import and export certificates have all been networked verification.
Inner Mongolia enterprises can use paperless methods to declare relevant documents to the customs, avoiding the past on-site rush, paper application, and repeated submission and other issues.
It is understood that the document preparation time refers to the preparation time of various documents required for the import and export links before the declaration, which is a major factor affecting the overall customs clearance time, and in order to reduce the customs clearance time and reduce the cost of customs clearance, the document must be reduced.
Previously in the import and export link need customs verification of various regulatory documents up to 86, involving 19 departments.
It is reported that in accordance with the principle that the "can be cancelled, the merger can be merged, can withdraw from the port verification of the exit port verification", relying on the "single window" platform of international trade, the customs and other 16 issuing authority system docking and data interconnection, to achieve more data running, enterprises less running errands.
The customs said that in the past, enterprises had to go back and forth to and from the relevant departments' on-site office hall to submit paper applications, and the process was long and unable to track the audit status in real time.
Now enterprise users can directly log in to the "single window" portal for online applications.
After the certification department is audited and approved, the electronic data transfer of the certificate will be transmitted to the customs, and the automatic comparison and intelligent verification of customs declaration data are realized in the customs clearance link, and the audit results are unified through the "single window" feedback to the enterprise, and the whole process of regulatory document declaration, audit, customs clearance and feedback is processed online.
