A three-way trade deal between the US and Canada will bring new opportunities for half a billion people.
According to foreign media reports, the Canadian Foreign Minister Freeland and U.S. Trade Representative Robert Lighthizer said in a joint statement published on the Canadian government's website that the United States, Canada and Mexico reached a three-way trade agreement, which will be called the "USMCA" (the three-state agreement between the United States and Mexico).
