In recent years, there have been incidents of unqualified campus plastic runways in many places.
To this end, the Ministry of Education issued a notice requiring that the use of primary and secondary school synthetic material surface sports venues after November 1st this year must implement the new national standard.
Mandified national standard "Semi-cell composite material surface sports venue" led by the Ministry of Education, 26 scientific research institutes and testing institutions participated in the drafting, after more than two years of revision, during the organization of more than 100 expert meeting demonstration, as well as nationwide field visits, sampling inspection, collected hundreds of enterprises on the market products countless verification experiments.
The reporter found that the new national standard not only changed from the "national recommended standard" to the "national mandatory standard", but also added many contents, including thickness requirements, physical properties, aging resistance, inorganic filler content requirements, anti-slip pellet high-polymer content requirements, surface limits for harmful substances in finished products, and limited quantities of harmful substances in non-solid and solid raw materials.
In particular, it is worth mentioning that the new national standard has limited the harmful substances that may be produced in the construction of the plastic runway on campus, increasing from the original seven to 18, and the limit of volatile organic matter of the runway after the completion of the home improvement has been stipulated.
If the "potped and prefabricated surface finished product in the harmful substances limit and odor requirements" clearly stipulates the release of harmful substances, the total volatile organic compounds shall not be higher than 5 mg / cubic meter, formaldehyde shall not be higher than 0.4 milligrams / cubic meters, carbon sulfide shall not be higher than 7 milligrams / cubic meters, benzene shall not be higher than 0.1 mg / cubic meters, odor level shall not be higher than level 3.
The new national standard also makes detailed provisions on the sampling requirements, inspection rules, and judgment rules of the plastic runway on the primary and secondary school campuses.
In addition, the campus artificial turf is also included in the scope of mandatory testing of the national standard for the first time.
In the near future, all localities should carry out special work and deployment on the implementation of the new national standard, and submit the implementation of the new national standard to the Department of Sports Health and Art Education of the Ministry of Education within the past year.
