From November 1st, China will reduce the most-favoured-nation tax rate on some commodities, and the total tariff level will be reduced to 7.5%
According to the decision of the 26th Standing Meeting of the State Council, the Tariff and Tax Committee of the State Council issued an announcement on the 30th, and since November 1, 2018, the most-favoured-nation tax rate for some commodities has been reduced.
According to the "Declaration of the Tariff Committee of the State Council on Reducing Import Tariffs for Some Commodities", in order to adapt to industrial upgrading, reduce the cost of enterprises and meet the multi-level consumption of the masses, the most-favored-nation tax rate on some industrial goods and other commodities will be reduced from November 1st this year.
A total of 1585 tax items on tax items, accounting for about 19% of the total number of tax items in China, the average tax rate has fallen from 10.5% to 7.8%, and the average reduction is 26%.
The tax reduction mainly involves textiles; stone, ceramics, glass products; some steel and base metal products; mechanical and electrical equipment and parts, such as metal processing machinery, textile machinery, construction machinery, transmission and substation equipment, electrical equipment, instrumentation, etc.; resource commodities and primary processing products, such as non-metal ore, inorganic chemicals, wood and paper products, gemstones, etc.
At the same time, with the reduction of the total tariff level, especially the import tariff on pharmaceuticals and daily consumer goods, the tax rate of import tax on imported goods is lowered accordingly.
In order to implement the decision-making and deployment of the Party Central Committee and the State Council, China has implemented zero tariffs on the vast majority of imported drugs from May 1st this year, reducing the import duties of automobiles and parts and parts of daily consumer goods from July 1st, and implemented the third step of the reduction of the information technology agreement to expand the product.
The reporter learned from the Tariff and Tax Committee of the State Council that since the beginning of this year, after successive independent adjustments, the total level of tariffs in China will be reduced from 9.8% to 7.5% from the previous year, and the average reduction has reached 23%.
The appropriate reduction of tariffs is conducive to promoting the balanced development of foreign trade and promoting a higher level of opening up, and it will also help to make overall use of both international and domestic resources and promote domestic supply-side structural reform.
The relevant person in charge of the committee said that this year marks the 40th anniversary of reform and opening up, and taking the initiative to reduce the overall level of tariffs is a practical action to implement the spirit of General Secretary Xi Jinping's important speech at the Boao Forum for Asia, and it is also an important measure for China to further expand opening-up and take the initiative to expand imports according to its own high-quality development needs. This action and measures show that China will unswervingly pursue a mutually beneficial and win-wining strategy of opening-up, while enhancing its own development momentum.
