Under the strong promotion of the embassy, the Mongolian side sent a rescue team for the first time and promised to waive the cost of search and rescue.
The General Directorate of Police and the General Directorate of Emergency Situations have instructed the police and emergency departments of the province of Kusugur to do their utmost to search and rescue.
Due to the fact that Lake Kusugur is located on the border between northern Mongolia and Russia, it is remote, the transportation and communication are extremely inconvenient, and the current Mongolia has entered a severe winter, the temperature is as low as minus 20 degrees, the local police and the emergency department have overcome great difficulties, almost all the police force, and launched local herders, through horse riding, walking, visiting the herdsmen, etc., around the missing location of the two to carry out carpet search and rescue.
At the same time, in view of the special situation of the pastoral area, the Mongolian side has been publishing the search notice through the broadcast loop for many days.
The relevant staff of the domestic blue sky rescue team has also come to Mongolia to actively participate in the rescue with the Mongolian side.
The safety of the two missing people has always touched our hearts.
So far, the two have been missing contact for more than ten days, and the embassy has received some clues, but still has not found the two, and the search and rescue operation is still under intense progress.
The Embassy will always follow the principle of "people-oriented" and continue to pay attention to this matter, promote the Mongolian side to continue its efforts in search and rescue, and provide maximum assistance to the families of the parties concerned.
The Embassy appealed to the Chinese Embassy in Mongolia to contact the Chinese Embassy in Mongolia if they learned about the relevant clues.
